Help Units

Ba +

Vacuum wavelengths for all transitions are provided in nm. The absolute values of the reduced electric-dipole (E1) matrix elements are in atomic units (\(ea_0\)), where \(e\) is elementary charge and \(a_0\) is the Bohr radius. We use the conventional system of atomic units, a.u., in which \(e\), the electron mass \(m_e\), and the reduced Planck constant have the numerical value 1, and the electric constant \(\epsilon_0\) has the numerical value \(1/(4\pi)\). E1 matrix elements in a.u. can be converted to SI units by using the conversion 1 a.u. of E1 matrix elements = 8.4783536255 \(\times 10^{-30}\) C\(\cdot\)m.
